Griffin-Benefit Street Partners BDC Corp. Key Developments

Griffin-Benefit Street Partners BDC Corp. Announces Resignation of Richard J. Byrne as Director
Jul 26 17
Griffin-Benefit Street Partners BDC Corp. announced that on July 20, 2017, Richard J. Byrne, a director of the Registrant, informed the company of his resignation as a director of the company effective July 31, 2017. Mr. Byrne's resignation is not due to any disagreement on any matter relating to the it’s operations, policies or practices. Mr. Byrne has served as a director of the company since its formation in May 2014.


Griffin-Benefit Street Partners BDC Corp., Annual General Meeting, Dec 13, 2016
Oct 20 16
Griffin-Benefit Street Partners BDC Corp., Annual General Meeting, Dec 13, 2016, at 10:00 Pacific Standard Time. Location: Griffin Capital Plaza, 1520 E. Grand Avenue El Segundo, CA 90245 United States Agenda: To consider the election of two directors, each for a term of three years; to ratify the appointment of Ernst & Young LLP as independent registered public accounting firm for the year ending December 31, 2016; and to transact such other business as may properly come before the meeting.


Griffin-Benefit Street Partners BDC Corp. Announces Management Changes
Mar 29 16
Effective March 23, 2016, John Canning, the Griffin-Benefit Street Partners BDC Corp.'s Chief Compliance Officer ("CCO"), in connection with his resignation as a Senior Managing Director at Cipperman Compliance Services, LLC ("Cipperman"), the company's third party compliance firm, resigned from his position as the company's CCO. In connection with Mr. Canning's departure from Cipperman, on March 23, 2016, the company's board of directors (the "Board"), after consultation with Cipperman, appointed Jay Haas, age 45, to serve as the company's CCO. Mr.  Haas serves as one of the compliance directors at Cipperman, a position he has held since October 2014, where he is responsible for compliance testing, maintaining compliance calendars and manuals, overseeing regulatory filings, preparing annual review reports, conducting sub-advisor due diligence reviews, and assisting in regulatory examinations for various mutual fund companies, investment advisors, and broker-dealers. Mr.  Haas has more than 18 years of experience in the financial services industry. Prior to joining Cipperman, from May 2006 to October 2014, Mr. Haas worked at The Vanguard Group, an investment management company, where he served as the Risk Manager and Compliance Manager. In addition, Mr. Haas served in various other positions, including: Vice President, Director of Compliance for Ferris Baker Watts Inc. from 2004 to 2006.


